# VidKeep Environment Configuration

# This project uses separate .env files for backend and frontend services.
# Docker Compose injects environment variables directly into services.

# Backend Configuration
# See: backend/.env.example
# - DATABASE_URL: PostgreSQL connection string
# - REDIS_URL: Redis connection string
# - DATA_PATH: Local path for storing downloaded videos
# - MAX_VIDEO_HEIGHT: Maximum video resolution (1080 for 1080p)

# Frontend Configuration
# See: frontend/.env.example
# - VITE_API_URL: Backend API URL (defaults to http://localhost:8000)
# - VITE_APP_NAME: Application name
# - VITE_APP_VERSION: Application version

# For local development with docker-compose:
# Docker Compose passes environment variables directly to containers.
# No .env file needs to be created at root level.

# To run with custom values, pass them to docker-compose:
# docker-compose -e VITE_API_URL=https://api.example.com up
